## D8. What §2.5 does NOT do — end-to-end SHUD simulation is scope-deferred
# The §2.3 synthetic package is a **direct-grid CONTRACT fixture**: it carries
# only the direct-grid-specific inputs (`.sp.att` with multi-station FORC,
# `.tsd.forc` multi-station forcing header, per-station CSVs, binding-manifest).
# It is NOT a full SHUD project — it is missing the other input files SHUD
# needs to actually simulate: `.sp.mesh` (mesh triangulation), `.sp.riv`
# (river network), `.sp.rivseg` (river segments), `.para.lc/geol/soil` (LC/geology/
# soil parameter sets), `.tsd.lai/mf/rl` (time-series LAI/melt-factor/roughness),
# and `.cfg.para/calib/ic` (config + calibration + initial conditions).
#
# Reference: a real 4773-element SHUD basin like `/scratch/frd_muziyao/NWM/SHUD/
# input/qhh/` has 18 input files spanning ~2 MiB; our 3-element synth has 6
# input files (plus manifest+sidecars) totaling ~2.5 KiB. Full simulation of
# the synth basin requires either:
#   (a) extending §2.3 synthetic package with a full multi-station SHUD input
#       tree (out of §2.3 scope; would require re-doing §2.3 evidence);
#   (b) operator-staged 3-element real basin (out of scope; would require a
#       small basin migration outside the readiness gate);
#   (c) grafting synth `.sp.att`/`.tsd.forc` into an existing project like qhh
#       (element-count mismatch: qhh=4773 vs synth=3, would corrupt qhh).
#
# All three paths are deferred to a follow-up change scope after Epic #886
# closes. §2.5 discharges the *staging* invariants (D4-D7) and records the
# *production* SHUD binary identity (D1-D3), which is the load-bearing
# evidence tasks.md §2.5 required-evidence bullets ask for.

